CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 4, 1950, pg. 2, reads: "Signs Removed - Now that union picket signs have been removed by force of a temporary court injunction, pupils at Letsche and other schools can be assured that school...go on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two men wearing sandwich boards reading: "A.F. of L. members employed by Pittsburgh Board of Education are locked out of their jobs by unfair action by Pittsburgh Board of Education"
